title: LIVING WITH YOURSELF Ending Explained!
author: Think Story
comment: The Ant-Man prequel we didn't know we needed 🐜
Did anyone else notice how the title sequence goes crazier in each  episode which symbolizes how miles life is going more and more unstable

A 50 year old man believably playing a 37 year old.
Paul Rudd is a gift to the human race.
I love how there is technically 2-3 episodes, but there are multiple episodes that show each characters part of the story.
The saddest part was that the little girl had the unicorn. Showing that children are just naturally happy and carefree. The older we get, the harder it is to achieve.
